Better than ordinary convection ovens - 360° quick cook technology and five super powerful heating elements mean your meals cook evenly on all sides in a whirlwind of super-heated air for crispy, delicious flavors. No added fats, oils, or unhealthy grease required. Get chef-quality results in one compact, 1500-watt countertop oven - 40% faster than regular ovens.

Extra versatile – LCD digital display with 12 cooking functions: air fry, bake, rotisserie, dehydrate, toast, reheat, roast, broil, bagel, pizza, slow cook, and Warm/ reheat. Using an air fryer over a traditional deep fryer can help reduce the number of unhealthy CALORIES you consume by up to 70% while still letting you enjoy your favorite foods.

Rotisserie stand not included-stainless-steel construction – a sleek, state-of-the art appliance to complement your kitchen and surrounding accessories, This All-in-One air fryer, rotisserie, and Dehydrator oven provides long-lasting versatility and an XL 930 cubic inch capacity. Includes a crisper tray, rotisserie spit, pizza rack, baking pan, drip tray, and cook book with recipes written by Emeril himself!

Trusted Emeril Lagasse Quality – every multi-purpose hot air fryer we produce is backed by chef-quality design, construction, and support to ensure it lasts through every evening meal, holiday dinner, and quick bite of delicious fries!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Everything I wanted in an oven/air fryer .
reviews.reviewText: I really enjoy using this oven. It is stainless steel very compact and it’s beautifully in my kitchen since I got this oven I have not even turned on my stove oven at all. This works even better than my stove and my phone comes out delicious crisp and just the way I like it. I also like that stainless seal and there’s no toxic chemicals in it all the accessories that comes with it or amazing, my son enjoys using this as well and now makes a lot of food in it and meal prep.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this toaster oven!
reviews.reviewText: I purchased several toaster oven/air fryer combos and returned them before buying this one. It does everything it is suppose to do. I love that it has an inside light, which most do not. It is easy to keep an eye on the food I am cooking, I also love that it remembers my settings…for example the desired darkness that I want my toast. The controls are very easy to use which I was looking for due to some knobs on the other brands being too difficult to turn. I’ve had it over 2 months and use it every day. I was a little hesitant to go with this brand instead of a more traditional toaster oven brand, but I have been very happy with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Where has this been all my life???
reviews.reviewText: Quick to heat, several settings, easy to clean. I can't believe I waited so long to get this air fryer/convection oven. LOVE IT.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I love the oven!
reviews.reviewText: I use this oven as my primary oven. Not perfect for Christmas Cookie Production, but the rest of the year it works for one person. My only complaint is that the racks fall forward when pulling them out - which has you pan or dish sliding towards you and hot! It is pretty easy to clean. It is not built for rotating large items. A Cornish Game Hen is too big! It makes the perfect gift for the graduate moving out and into their own place for the first time. The top gets hot, so don't use the oven top for storage of anything meltable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good with minor design deficiencies
reviews.reviewText: Compared to similar in size Breville 670: on the good side, this one would make frozen waffles quite decent on bagel setting. Also, I like steel heaters that are more reliable than quartz when are dripped over, and I do like the absence of "smart chip" that does something without explanations. Emeril algorithm is much simpler, well explained in the manual, and therefore the result is predictable. However, the Breville oven looks more expensive (which it is). I was not too successful making french fries on air-fry setting, but that could be just me. Baking is fine.What I do not like about Emeril:- the LCD display loses contrast if placed at your eye level or higher (Breville's LCD is as bad. They say more expensive Breville models have much better displays, but alas they are much bigger, and I wanted a mini oven, not a major appliance).- the LCD display is too busy, and functions are hard to read- the main control knob is the smallest one - an idiotic design choice, if you ask me. When you choose the function, it rotates too easy, and you have to be careful to select the right one. Two large knobs are for secondary settings, which is counterintuitive, so Breville wins this round.- the buttons are marked not very clearly- the beep is not overly loud, but could wake up someone else, and not sure if it can be turned off.So, overall, the oven seems worth its money, and I do not regret the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I read most reviews and can address a few issues. My spouse and I are also older and experienced cooks. First, cover your drip pan with foil before you cook anything. The burning and warping issues will disappear. Also cover your "pizza" pan with foil. These pans are not high quality and will be ruined quickly if you don't add a layer of protection. The airfryer function is just okay. I have used it twice but prefer my one function air fryer. For baking, we reduce the heat by 10 degrees and check it way before stated cook times. The baking feature tends to overcook. We did a 4 lbs. Rotisserie chicken tonight. We have a weber charcoal/wood grill with a Rotisserie, and we had the best chicken ever with this oven. You must tie it up with kitchen string though and really balance the chicken when skewering. Test it by skewering and turning it in your hands to test the balance before placing it in the oven. I included a picture to help with the visuals. Fall off the bone good but we cut the cooking time to 50 minutes. Also, keep plenty of space around your oven. People aren't kidding about the heat it puts out and I accidentally burned my forearm on the outside top of the oven when I reached over to unplug it.Update! We successfully cooked a 6 pound chicken. It was succulent and amazing. I would NOT do anything bigger than that.

I bought this item to replace my original Emeril Lagasse air fryer which I have basically used every day since purchasing it several years ago. Finally the door hinge gave out. If we are able to repair it, we will relocate it to the cottage. I love the multiple functionality of this product. The food cooks beautifully and it is ideal in our two person household.

I really like the Air Fryer but it would be nice to know where to find the basket to buy and this is because when he demonstrates this Air fryer it shows him using 3 of the basket at the same time. In the package it only supplies one of these it would be nice to have the 3 to use at the same time.

I purchased this item from Amazon strictly because it was Amazon. I have had to return an item to Amazon in the past and they were very helpful. My one serious complaint with this item is the price. I paid $ 338 or so Canadian. This same unit was for sale and in stock at Wal-Mart on the same day for $ 249.00 Canadian. The larger XL version could be purchased from W/M for less than I paid for the unit in question. I guess I expected Amazon to be more competitive than it was in this case. I felt that if I unpacked the Wal-Mart unit ( not easy by the way ) and it proved defective/damaged, I would likely have had a real problem with a return to them given the high dollar amount. The unit itself is as advertised, no problem with it, just this nagging feeling that I may have "given away" nearly a hundred dollars.
Enjoy the warmth and its just the right size
